The paper deals with the study of CSS codes, which are a type of error-correcting codes used in quantum computing. The paper uses concepts from information theory, discrete mathematics, and computer science, which are covered by the sub-categories cs.IT, cs.DM, and cs.CC. The paper also discusses the behavior of iterated tensor powers of codes, which is related to the study of LDPC (low-density parity-check) codes, covered by the sub-category cs.DS. Finally, the paper proposes new families of CSS codes, which can be seen as a contribution to the field of coding theory, covered by the sub-category cs.SI.
